  },
  "xp_reward": 60,
  "story_variants": {
    "en": "## Vaathiyaar's Time Machine\n\nVaathiyaar adjusts dials on a time machine. \"How many days until the deadline? What day was 100 days ago? Is it business hours in Tokyo? The `datetime` module answers all time questions!\"\n\n### The datetime Module\n\n```python\nfrom datetime import datetime, timedelta\n\nnow = datetime.now()\nprint(now)  # 2025-03-27 14:30:00.123456\n```\n\n### Key Classes\n\n| Class | Purpose | Example |\n|-------|---------|----------|\n| `date` | Date only | `2025-03-27` |\n| `time` | Time only | `14:30:00` |\n| `datetime` | Date + Time | `2025-03-27 14:30:00` |\n| `timedelta` | Duration | `5 days, 3:00:00` |\n\n### Format Codes\n\n| Code | Meaning | Example |\n|------|---------|----------|\n| `%Y` | Year (4 digit) | 2025 |\n| `%m` | Month (01-12) | 03 |\n| `%d` | Day (01-31) | 27 |\n| `%H` | Hour (00-23) | 14 |\n| `%M` | Minute (00-59) | 30 |\n\n> **Key Concept:** `strftime` = string FROM time (formatting). `strptime` = string PARSE time (parsing). The 'f' and 'p' are the mnemonics."
  },
